<paragraph blockId="31.[189,303,1118,1144]" box="[189,303,1118,1144]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,1118,1144]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,1118,1144]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[189,1399,1164,1332]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<bibRefCitation author="Ebmer A. W." box="[189,416,1164,1191]" firstAuthor="Ebmer" journalOrPublisher="Linzer biologische Beitrage" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="205 - 288" part="8" refId="ref13032" refString="Ebmer A. W. 1976. Halictus and Lasioglossum aus Marokko. Linzer biologische Beitrage 8 (1): 205 - 288." title="Halictus and Lasioglossum aus Marokko" type="journal article" year="1976">Ebmer (1976: 251</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ebmer A. W." box="[433,559,1164,1191]" firstAuthor="Ebmer" journalOrPublisher="Linzer biologische Beitrage" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="527 - 711" part="20" refId="ref13210" refString="Ebmer A. W. 1988. Kritische Liste der nicht-parasitischen Halictidae Osterreichs mit Berucksichtigung aller mitteleuropaischen Arten (Insecta: Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Halictidae). Linzer biologische Beitrage 20 (2): 527 - 711." title="Kritische Liste der nicht-parasitischen Halictidae Osterreichs mit Berucksichtigung aller mitteleuropaischen Arten (Insecta: Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Halictidae)" type="journal article" year="1988">1988: 649</bibRefCitation>
) considers this species as valid, but 
<bibRefCitation author="Pesenko Y. A." box="[1020,1272,1164,1190]" firstAuthor="Pesenko" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="1 - 54" part="1500" refId="ref15564" refString="Pesenko Y. A. 2007 a. Subgeneric classification of the Palaearctic bees of the genus Evylaeus Robertson (Hymenoptera: Halictidae). Zootaxa 1500: 1 - 54." title="Subgeneric classification of the Palaearctic bees of the genus Evylaeus Robertson (Hymenoptera: Halictidae)" type="journal article" year="2007" yearSuffix="a">Pesenko (2007a: 41)</bibRefCitation>
following 
<bibRefCitation author="Warncke K." box="[189,427,1199,1225]" firstAuthor="Warncke" journalOrPublisher="Nachrichtenblatt der Bayerischen Entomologen" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="89 - 96" part="25" refId="ref17351" refString="Warncke K. 1976. Bemerkungen zu der Arbeit von Ebmer uber die als Apis beschriebenen Bienen der Gattung Halictus und ein Beitrag zur Namensklarung nordafrikanischer Bienen der gleichen Gattung (Hym. Apidae). Nachrichtenblatt der Bayerischen Entomologen 25 (5): 89 - 96." title="Bemerkungen zu der Arbeit von Ebmer uber die als Apis beschriebenen Bienen der Gattung Halictus und ein Beitrag zur Namensklarung nordafrikanischer Bienen der gleichen Gattung (Hym. Apidae)" type="journal article" year="1976">Warncke (1976: 94)</bibRefCitation>
mention it as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kirby" baseAuthorityYear="1802" box="[779,934,1199,1225]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="villosulum">
<emphasis box="[779,934,1199,1225]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">L. villosulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This small species of 
<quantity box="[1215,1286,1199,1226]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
length is very close to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kirby" baseAuthorityYear="1802" box="[345,498,1234,1260]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="villosulum">
<emphasis box="[345,498,1234,1260]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">L. villosulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but is well separated by its barcode. We have examined the 
<typeStatus box="[1209,1260,1235,1261]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">type</typeStatus>
and we can confirm that it differs from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kirby" baseAuthorityYear="1802" box="[522,677,1270,1296]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="villosulum">
<emphasis box="[522,677,1270,1296]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">L. villosulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the impunctate apical margin of the terga (
<figureCitation box="[1239,1350,1270,1296]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="33.[189,232,1965,1991]" captionTargetBox="[192,1399,449,1908]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[189,1399,449,1920]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Fig. 23. Lasioglossum berberum (Benoist, 1941), holotype, ♂. A. Head. B. Scutum. C. Propodeum. D. First tergum. E. Metasoma." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3377669/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Fig. 23D</figureCitation>
), as mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ebmer A. W." box="[357,583,1305,1332]" firstAuthor="Ebmer" journalOrPublisher="Linzer biologische Beitrage" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="205 - 288" part="8" refId="ref13032" refString="Ebmer A. W. 1976. Halictus and Lasioglossum aus Marokko. Linzer biologische Beitrage 8 (1): 205 - 288." title="Halictus and Lasioglossum aus Marokko" type="journal article" year="1976">Ebmer (1976: 251)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
